Package: mic.sim
Type: Package
Title: Simulating and Fitting Models to MIC Data
Version: 0.2.1
Author: Alec Michael
Maintainer: Alec Michael <alec.j.michael@gmail.com>
Description: mic.sim includes functions for analyzing minimum inhibitory concentration data,
    including functions for importing or simulating data, viewing the distribution, model
    fitting, and model visualization. The model fitting uses a latent Gaussian mixture
    model framework to analyze trends in the mixture weights and component means on the
    log2 MIC scale to attempt to distinguish and model the wild type and non-wild type
    subpopulations.
